01:24:43,417 --> 01:24:45,794
<i>It was my recon squad.</i>

679
01:24:46,003 --> 01:24:51,008
Their names are in the yearbook.
Liz was my friend.

680
01:24:55,512 --> 01:25:02,186
Thank you for your co-operation.
Someone from CID will be in touch.

681
01:25:05,939 --> 01:25:10,527
What are you doing?
What about the DNA?

682
01:25:10,736 --> 01:25:15,115
What DNA?
I bought those an hour ago.

683
01:25:15,324 --> 01:25:17,910
So long, honey.

684
01:25:44,603 --> 01:25:48,148
<i>- That's a positive match?
- It's only a partial print.</i>

685
01:25:48,357 --> 01:25:52,736
<i>But it's definitely Fowler's,
and it's right next to the body.</i>

686
01:25:52,945 --> 01:25:57,115
We only have today,
then the Feds will be all over us.

687
01:25:59,535 --> 01:26:03,997
- I got a lot on my plate just now.
- I just want to thank you.

688
01:26:04,206 --> 01:26:07,751
For leaving the medical records
in the car.

689
01:26:09,419 --> 01:26:13,924
- Did he instruct you to do it?
- Not in so many words.

690
01:26:14,133 --> 01:26:18,929
I knew his wishes. Anything to help.
You know how much he loved her.

691
01:26:19,138 --> 01:26:22,975
- Not as much as he loved you.
- What do you mean?

692
01:26:23,183 --> 01:26:29,857
The way you came in that night,
the extra care in making dinner.

693
01:26:30,190 --> 01:26:32,568
- What do you plan on doing?
- Not a thing.

694
01:26:32,901 --> 01:26:37,072
Other than to say I'm sorry
and ask for your help.

695
01:26:37,281 --> 01:26:42,995
- What do you need to know about?
- The recreation of the rape.

696
01:26:43,203 --> 01:26:47,791
- I suppose that's what it was.
- Was it Moore's idea to do this?

697
01:26:48,000 --> 01:26:52,296
- To cleanse her of her past?
- Jesus, no. She thought it up.

698
01:26:52,504 --> 01:26:58,552
- He couldn't talk her out of it.
- He felt so bad he killed himself?

699
01:26:58,760 --> 01:27:01,138
We both know
that's not how it happened.

700
01:27:01,346 --> 01:27:05,100
That's where they screwed up,
whoever did this.

701
01:27:05,309 --> 01:27:08,437
They didn't know about Bob and me.

702
01:27:09,271 --> 01:27:13,650
Bob could never have killed himself.

703
01:27:13,984 --> 01:27:17,112
These types don't understand that.

704
01:27:17,321 --> 01:27:20,240
Affairs of the heart
are beyond them.

705
01:27:20,449 --> 01:27:26,371
Okay, so he staged this thing.
Tied her up, got rid of her clothes?

706
01:27:26,580 --> 01:27:29,833
And he had to call the general,
play him the tape.

707
01:27:30,542 --> 01:27:32,002
The tape?

708
01:27:49,228 --> 01:27:51,730
General ... Brenner.

709
01:28:02,783 --> 01:28:06,620
Paul, come in, please.

710
01:28:10,582 --> 01:28:14,545
Just wanted to say goodbye, sir.
I'm leaving in the morning.

711
01:28:14,878 --> 01:28:19,550
I'm leaving tomorrow, too.
I'm taking Elisabeth to Michigan -

712
01:28:19,758 --> 01:28:23,512
- to be buried next to her mother.

713
01:28:23,720 --> 01:28:28,225
Thank you for everything you did.

714
01:28:28,433 --> 01:28:31,645
I understand
you're still going into politics?

715
01:28:31,979 --> 01:28:34,773
The jury's still out. We'll see.

716
01:28:38,235 --> 01:28:42,406
When you thanked me for what
I had done, what I wanted to say -

717
01:28:42,614 --> 01:28:46,034
- was I really didn't do anything.

718
01:28:46,243 --> 01:28:49,997
Not anything right. I did
a lot of things that were wrong.

719
01:28:50,205 --> 01:28:55,210
You're not responsible for Moore's
death. You followed your instincts.

720
01:28:55,544 --> 01:28:58,964
I'd like to talk about that, sir.

721
01:28:59,173 --> 01:29:03,552
- We all know Moore did it.
- Then we're all in agreement.

722
01:29:03,760 --> 01:29:10,017
But what if it wasn't one car three
times, but three different cars?

723
01:29:10,976 --> 01:29:15,230
What difference does it make,
since Moore is dead?

724
01:29:15,564 --> 01:29:21,069
It got me thinking about
your daughter, and what she taught.

725
01:29:23,280 --> 01:29:27,659
''Mostly we fuck with
people's minds,'' she said.

726
01:29:28,494 --> 01:29:32,539
Thank you, Brenner.
You can go now.

727
01:29:35,042 --> 01:29:37,669
- Tell me about the rape.
- But she wasn't raped.

728
01:29:37,878 --> 01:29:40,380
It was just made to appear that way.

729
01:29:41,632 --> 01:29:44,968
The rape at West Point.

730
01:29:45,177 --> 01:29:48,514
It was kept confidential
for the good of the academy.

731
01:29:48,722 --> 01:29:53,727
And the army.
And it was best for Elisabeth.

732
01:29:53,936 --> 01:29:59,358
- You were in Germany?
- Berlin. I was stationed there.

733
01:29:59,566 --> 01:30:04,655
- I came back as soon as I heard.
- You went straight from the plane?

734
01:30:04,863 --> 01:30:07,991
- Of course.
- No meeting first?

735
01:30:12,704 --> 01:30:18,627
- Mr Brenner is very well informed.
- It was in her psych records, sir.

736
01:30:18,836 --> 01:30:21,964
It didn't happen that way.

737
01:30:22,172 --> 01:30:28,137
George, he's right.
The meeting did come first.

738
01:30:30,430 --> 01:30:34,268
It was seven years ago.
The details get confusing.

739
01:30:34,476 --> 01:30:38,647
It was nothing. A quick briefing
in a hotel near the Point.

740
01:30:38,856 --> 01:30:44,695
General Sonenberg.
He was very sympathetic.

741
01:30:45,863 --> 01:30:50,033
I want justice for my daughter.

742
01:30:50,242 --> 01:30:55,038
I would give anything if this
had never happened. But it did.

743
01:30:55,247 --> 01:31:01,795
I'm telling you the reality of the
situation. We'll never find them.

744
01:31:02,004 --> 01:31:08,469
But we do know that a co-ed academy
is a good and necessary call.

745
01:31:08,677 --> 01:31:11,805
Better one unreported
and unvindicated rape -

746
01:31:12,014 --> 01:31:15,476
- than to shake the foundations
of West Point.

747
01:31:15,684 --> 01:31:21,732
To cast suspicion on a thousand
soldiers who did not gang-rape her.

748
01:31:21,940 --> 01:31:26,111
All we have to do
is convince your daughter -

749
01:31:26,320 --> 01:31:32,242
- that she, the Academy,
the army and the cause of equality -

750
01:31:32,576 --> 01:31:37,873
- would be best served if she
just forgot about the whole thing.

751
01:31:38,081 --> 01:31:41,752
These are the times we live in, Joe.

752
01:31:42,586 --> 01:31:46,423
He was right.
If it had gone public, -

753
01:31:46,757 --> 01:31:52,262
- it would have permanently
damaged women in the military.

754
01:31:52,471 --> 01:31:58,310
- It would've destroyed West Point.
- Is that what you told Elisabeth?

755
01:31:59,144 --> 01:32:02,606
Not in so many words, no.

756
01:32:03,941 --> 01:32:08,529
She was in no condition
to understand that then.

757
01:32:08,737 --> 01:32:11,865
I simply tried to tell her
that I loved her.

758
01:32:15,536 --> 01:32:17,913
I loved her very much.

759
01:32:18,664 --> 01:32:25,003
Daddy loves you.
And he's so proud of you.

760
01:32:26,672 --> 01:32:31,051
Rest now.
Try not to think about it anymore.

761
01:32:32,636 --> 01:32:37,307
Listen to me.
I only want what's best for you.

762
01:32:39,101 --> 01:32:46,191
Trust me.
Do you? Like you always did?

763
01:32:49,528 --> 01:32:53,282
Then don't ever think about
any of this again.

764
01:32:54,199 --> 01:32:59,830
I know. It's an awful thing.
A terrible, terrible thing.

765
01:33:00,164 --> 01:33:05,586
But thinking about it won't help it.
So ...

766
01:33:07,963 --> 01:33:12,468
Close your eyes.

767
01:33:12,676 --> 01:33:15,679
It never happened.

768
01:33:15,888 --> 01:33:19,850
None of this ever happened.

769
01:33:45,834 --> 01:33:48,337
Not my finest hour.

770
01:33:48,545 --> 01:33:52,925
You were just doing what you said,
trying to protect her.

771
01:33:53,133 --> 01:33:56,345
I did what I had to.

772
01:33:56,553 --> 01:34:00,641
What I thought best
for everyone concerned.

773
01:34:00,849 --> 01:34:06,271
Nothing else could've been done.
They never would have found them.

774
01:34:10,651 --> 01:34:12,945
- Here you are, sir.
- What is that?

775
01:34:14,404 --> 01:34:21,078
The names of the perpetrators,
found with a minimum of trouble.

776
01:34:22,538 --> 01:34:27,543
- That's just brilliant.
- Each man will get 20 years.

777
01:34:27,751 --> 01:34:31,588
- I think you'd better go now.
- Fine.

778
01:34:31,797 --> 01:34:37,010
We'll deal with the phone call issue
tomorrow, before your flight.

779
01:34:38,178 --> 01:34:40,347
What phone call issue?

780
01:34:40,556 --> 01:34:45,978
I have reason to believe Moore
phoned you the night of the murder.

781
01:34:48,188 --> 01:34:50,357
Why would he have done that?

782
01:34:50,691 --> 01:34:55,988
I think the whole recreation
of the rape was Elisabeth's idea.

783
01:34:56,321 --> 01:35:02,244
You were going into politics. Maybe
she thought it was her last chance.

784
01:35:02,452 --> 01:35:07,166
She got Moore to put her in the
same position that the rapists did.

785
01:35:07,374 --> 01:35:13,213
You weren't in Germany. She wanted
you to see what you covered up.

786
01:35:13,422 --> 01:35:18,093
- That never happened!
- A gift from Moore's lawyer.

787
01:35:19,470 --> 01:35:23,432
<i>Dad, this is Elisabeth. I need to
discuss something urgent with you.</i>

788
01:35:23,640 --> 01:35:27,686
<i>Meet me at the mount site
no later than 03:30 hours.</i>

789
01:35:27,895 --> 01:35:31,440
<i>I have an answer to your ultimatum.</i>

790
01:35:32,608 --> 01:35:37,404
You can't argue with a recording.
I'm sure it was part of her plan.

791
01:35:37,613 --> 01:35:41,033
What does she mean by an ultimatum?

792
01:35:41,366 --> 01:35:43,452
I gave her two options:

793
01:35:43,660 --> 01:35:49,082
Resign her commission,
or agree to some sort of therapy.

794
01:35:49,291 --> 01:35:55,756
If she rejected both, I'd instruct
the staff judge advocate -

795
01:35:55,964 --> 01:35:59,176
- to draw up charges
for a general court martial.

796
01:35:59,384 --> 01:36:06,058
- That must seem callous to you.
- You drove out to the mount site?

797
01:36:06,809 --> 01:36:10,437
Of course. I needed an answer.

798
01:36:13,148 --> 01:36:17,444
Here's the answer
to your damn ultimatum.

799
01:36:17,653 --> 01:36:21,698
Do you see what they did to me?
Do you see?

800
01:36:21,907 --> 01:36:28,497
Don't turn away. Come closer.
See what they put me through!

801
01:36:28,705 --> 01:36:32,876
What the fuck
do you hope to accomplish?

802
01:36:33,085 --> 01:36:39,007
There's a rope around my neck.
Strangle me or cover it up again.

803
01:36:39,216 --> 01:36:43,720
Have you gone
completely out of your mind?

804
01:36:43,929 --> 01:36:46,098
It happened.

805
01:36:46,306 --> 01:36:51,228
It happened!
I want to hear you say it happened!

806
01:36:51,436 --> 01:36:56,525
I don't give a damn what
happened to you seven years ago.

807
01:36:56,733 --> 01:37:00,904
Whatever hurts you
makes me stronger.

808
01:37:01,655 --> 01:37:05,492
You can't hurt me anymore.

809
01:37:07,786 --> 01:37:11,039
- We're even.
- That's fine with me.

810
01:37:12,166 --> 01:37:15,919
You never helped me!

811
01:37:16,128 --> 01:37:19,256
Daddy, please don't go.

812
01:37:19,590 --> 01:37:22,926
Come back. Please.

813
01:37:23,135 --> 01:37:25,304
Please ...

814
01:37:28,640 --> 01:37:31,268
Daddy ...

815
01:37:40,736 --> 01:37:44,072
So you were in the second car.

816
01:37:44,281 --> 01:37:50,245
Which means Col. Fowler
must have been in the third.

817
01:37:53,373 --> 01:37:56,710
You couldn't expect a man
to deal with his own child.

818
01:37:56,919 --> 01:38:01,089
She was screaming
such vituperations at him.

819
01:38:03,050 --> 01:38:05,886
Of course not.

820
01:38:06,094 --> 01:38:10,557
So he called me.
And he asked me to deal with it.

821
01:38:12,017 --> 01:38:16,939
I went ... and I found her dead.

822
01:38:19,942 --> 01:38:23,612
- You found her dead?
- Of course.

823
01:38:24,738 --> 01:38:29,535
But you will never get me
to testify against the general.

824
01:38:30,494 --> 01:38:31,745
What?

825
01:38:31,954 --> 01:38:36,834
I've been by Joe Campbell's side
too many times.

826
01:38:38,210 --> 01:38:43,215
Looked death in the face with him
too many times.

827
01:38:43,423 --> 01:38:48,720
- I'll not back down now.
- What are you talking about?

828
01:38:48,929 --> 01:38:52,683
It wasn't like
she didn't give him reason.

829
01:38:53,016 --> 01:38:58,730
- George, for Christ's sake!
- And when we realised ...

830
01:38:59,773 --> 01:39:03,944
... she was fucking everybody ...

831
01:39:04,278 --> 01:39:09,700
... from Bill Kent to Jake Elby,
it was too late for official action.

832
01:39:10,409 --> 01:39:12,077
Col. Fowler!

833
01:39:12,411 --> 01:39:16,165
You'd have to ask for
all their resignations.

834
01:39:16,373 --> 01:39:21,587
- Strangulation, you think?
- And then resign ourselves.

835
01:39:21,795 --> 01:39:25,424
You need civilian authority.
What happened to you?

836
01:39:28,760 --> 01:39:33,557
- You had no choice, sir.
- You think I killed my daughter?

837
01:39:34,308 --> 01:39:40,981
- It'll die with me, Joe.
- You sorry son of a bitch!

838
01:39:41,190 --> 01:39:43,984
- Bill, where's Moore?
- He was released.

839
01:39:49,615 --> 01:39:52,743
Cal, it's me.
Let me speak to Sunhill.

840
01:39:52,951 --> 01:39:58,165
She got in an hour ago,
then went out to the crime scene.

841
01:39:58,373 --> 01:40:02,461
She took the big dog with her.
Capt. America himself.

842
01:40:02,669 --> 01:40:07,132
<i>Kent. It was his idea.
He wants you to meet him there.</i>

843
01:40:07,466 --> 01:40:10,469
Of course he does.

844
01:40:26,527 --> 01:40:29,655
Sunhill!

845
01:40:33,116 --> 01:40:38,205
We've been through this place
a dozen times before.

846
01:40:45,212 --> 01:40:50,092
- Paul?
- Sure, sure ... Paul.

847
01:40:53,554 --> 01:40:56,765
The three of us need to go back
to your office and talk.

848
01:40:57,724 --> 01:41:04,606
Why don't we talk here, if we have
anything important to talk about?

849
01:41:04,815 --> 01:41:07,818
I thought you'd pin it on Moore
and move on.

850
01:41:09,403 --> 01:41:14,700
- Oh, God.
- I forgot you were a nasty rat.

851
01:41:15,033 --> 01:41:19,621
- Just goes to show you.
- Why did you do it?

852
01:41:19,830 --> 01:41:24,084
Why?
You tell me, you're the expert.

853
01:41:24,293 --> 01:41:28,881
She gave it out all over the post.
The one man who cared about her, -

854
01:41:29,089 --> 01:41:32,968
- the one willing to risk it all,
is the person she doesn't want.

855
01:41:33,177 --> 01:41:36,722
And that's because
she couldn't want anybody.

856
01:41:44,521 --> 01:41:48,192
I just wanted to be with her.
She owned my heart.

857
01:41:49,860 --> 01:41:54,948
<i>She tormented me.
She became my obsession.</i>

858
01:41:57,659 --> 01:42:01,747
<i>So I followed her,
and found her on the range.</i>

859
01:42:01,955 --> 01:42:03,707
<i>On display.</i>

860
01:42:04,750 --> 01:42:09,046
- Elisabeth?
- Get the fuck out of here.

861
01:42:10,714 --> 01:42:14,134
He'll come back. You can't be here.
You'll ruin it all.

862
01:42:15,928 --> 01:42:21,433
- What's all this about?
- Did my father send you?

863
01:42:21,767 --> 01:42:26,772
- Did he send you to shut me up?
- No.

864
01:42:26,980 --> 01:42:32,069
Well, this time I won't be quiet.
This time I'll tell everything.

865
01:42:32,277 --> 01:42:38,742
About him, about you.
I'll tell your wife, your kids ...

866
01:42:40,953 --> 01:42:44,373
Don't touch me!
Get your hands off me!

867
01:42:50,963 --> 01:42:53,340
You repulse me! You're a disgrace!

868
01:42:53,549 --> 01:42:58,470
You're not a soldier. You're not
even a man. You're just a fuck.

869
01:42:58,679 --> 01:43:01,473
I fucked you!

870
01:43:08,355 --> 01:43:10,649
Oh, Christ!

871
01:43:29,334 --> 01:43:33,088
Bill, let's get going.
Come on.

872
01:43:39,344 --> 01:43:42,139
I'm all yours, Paulie.

873
01:43:42,347 --> 01:43:47,561
Before you come closer, don't you
want to know where you're standing?

874
01:43:47,769 --> 01:43:51,857
- Where am I standing?
- In a minefield.

875
01:43:52,065 --> 01:43:56,445
I buried some Bouncing Betties.
Anti-personnel.

876
01:43:56,653 --> 01:44:02,367
You're reasonably safe,
but little Miss Can't-be Wrong ...

877
01:44:03,202 --> 01:44:05,913
She's deep in the hurt locker.

878
01:44:06,246 --> 01:44:11,543
You remember how the Betty works?
First man trips the primary, -

879
01:44:11,877 --> 01:44:16,340
- the rest of the column walks into
the blast. Heads, limbs ...

880
01:44:16,548 --> 01:44:18,842
Backtrack.

881
01:44:19,176 --> 01:44:22,596
What shrapnel does
to flesh and bone ...

882
01:44:22,805 --> 01:44:25,724
- Sarah, you're fine.
- God!

883
01:44:31,480 --> 01:44:35,526
- Scared you, didn't I?
- You're an asshole, Kent!

884
01:44:35,859 --> 01:44:38,654
Come on, Bill, it's over.

885
01:44:39,404 --> 01:44:40,948
Yeah, it's over.

886
01:44:45,869 --> 01:44:48,163
But not the way you think.

887
01:45:16,942 --> 01:45:21,405
Attention!
Present arms!

888
01:45:29,037 --> 01:45:32,666
<i>The human eye
can distinguish 16 shades of grey.</i>

889
01:45:32,875 --> 01:45:36,128
<i>A computer,
analysing a fingerprint, -</i>

890
01:45:36,336 --> 01:45:40,924
<i>- can distinguish 256 shades
of grey, which is impressive.</i>

891
01:45:41,133 --> 01:45:44,052
<i>The human heart,
mind and soul, however, -</i>

892
01:45:44,261 --> 01:45:49,766
<i>- can distinguish an infinite number
of emotional and moral shadings.</i>

893
01:45:49,975 --> 01:45:56,982
<i>In Psy Ops we deal with the blackest
of black and the whitest of white.</i>

894
01:46:01,028 --> 01:46:03,655
At ease, soldier.

895
01:46:09,912 --> 01:46:14,500
- Is Col. Fowler coming?
- He's taking much-needed R&R.

896
01:46:14,708 --> 01:46:20,839
He's a good man.
A good man and a good soldier.

897
01:46:21,048 --> 01:46:25,636
Sometimes the lines get blurred,
but when push comes to shove ...

898
01:46:25,844 --> 01:46:30,015
- He'll do what needs to be done.
- And what is that, sir?

899
01:46:30,766 --> 01:46:36,271
Say Moore called him,
and that I was never out there ...

900
01:46:36,480 --> 01:46:41,693
He'll do that for me,
even if it means his career.

901
01:46:41,902 --> 01:46:48,158
Like a good soldier.
Nothing is gained by my involvement.

902
01:46:49,535 --> 01:46:54,623
A letter of commendation
will be inserted into your file.

903
01:46:54,832 --> 01:47:00,170
In recognition of
your exemplary work on this case.

904
01:47:06,844 --> 01:47:10,806
Remember when I asked you
if you were a cop or a soldier?

905
01:47:11,014 --> 01:47:17,563
You're a soldier, Paul.
And a damn fine one.

906
01:47:27,698 --> 01:47:29,366
General Campbell ...

907
01:47:30,826 --> 01:47:35,414
- You're wrong. I'm a bad soldier.
- Oh? And why is that?

908
01:47:35,622 --> 01:47:38,625
You really don't get it, do you?

909
01:47:38,959 --> 01:47:44,882
The only mind Elisabeth
wanted to fuck with was yours.

910
01:47:45,841 --> 01:47:50,721
- And you still don't get it.
- I've done nothing wrong.

911
01:47:53,557 --> 01:47:58,979
- You killed her.
- What did you say?

912
01:48:00,314 --> 01:48:06,570
Seven years ago, when you told her
to forget about it, you killed her.

913
01:48:08,030 --> 01:48:13,452
- Kent killed her.
- He just put her out of her misery.

914
01:48:15,662 --> 01:48:20,542
I once asked Moore what was
worse than rape. Now I know.

915
01:48:21,376 --> 01:48:23,462
Betrayal.

916
01:48:23,670 --> 01:48:28,884
I loved Elisabeth, but there were
larger issues to consider.

917
01:48:29,092 --> 01:48:34,515
You traded her trust
for your career. You made a deal.

918
01:48:34,848 --> 01:48:38,477
You kept silent,
and they gave you another star.

919
01:48:38,685 --> 01:48:45,567
I'm going to say in my report
that you left her out there to die.

920
01:48:47,653 --> 01:48:51,824
- You don't have the balls.
- Oh, you're wrong, sir.

921
01:48:52,032 --> 01:48:58,413
- That's just about all I have left.
- You can kiss your career goodbye.

922
01:48:58,622 --> 01:49:04,128
I'll have you court-martialled, sir.
Conspiracy to conceal a crime.

923
01:49:38,871 --> 01:49:44,376
When this all started, I told you
we'd find the son of a bitch, sir.

924
01:49:45,544 --> 01:49:50,632
I never expected that
the son of a bitch would be you.

